PROVENANCE AND ORIGIN
======================================================================

Entropic was authored by Tristan VanFossen, who retains sole
copyright in the work. Entropic was consolidated from prior personal
projects developed outside working hours on the author's personal
hardware. The publicly visible predecessors include:

  - github.com/tvanfossen/local-llm-mcp
    (created 2025-08-27; description: "Predecessor to entropi.")

  - github.com/tvanfossen/pathfinder-society-scribe
    (created 2025-08-17; Discord bot using local LLM models with
    BDD-validated behavioral flows)

  - tvanfossen/homeschool-assistant
    (private repo; one of the original application contexts that
    motivated consolidation into a reusable engine)

The public commit histories on the personal account establish prior
art and timeline: foundational LLM-orchestration work on these
predecessor projects predates the genesis commit of Entropic
(2025-12-19) by four months or more. Entropic itself is the
consolidation of patterns and code that emerged across those earlier
personal projects.

The author subsequently extended Entropic during employment at
BISSELL Homecare Inc. — see "BISSELL HOMECARE INC. ACKNOWLEDGMENT"
below for the relationship and how the linking exception
acknowledges it.

Copyright in the consolidated engine rests with Tristan VanFossen
personally. The engine is intended for both personal and corporate
use; the licensing structure of this project (LGPL-3.0-or-later +
BISSELL Linking Exception) is designed so that both contexts have
unambiguous, on-record terms of use.

